      </m:math>
    </equation><para id="import-auto-id1562997">
      <title>Discussion for (a)</title>
      
    </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id2960580">This small value for the capacitance indicates how difficult it is to make a device with a large capacitance. Special techniques help, such as using very large area thin foils placed close together.</para>
    <para id="import-auto-id2507307">
      <title>Solution for (b)</title>
      
    </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id1357066">The charge stored in any capacitor is given by the equation <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>Q</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mstyle fontstyle="italic"><m:mrow><m:mtext>CV</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>. Entering the known values into this equation gives </para><equation id="eip-754"><m:math>
        
          <m:mrow>
